f the enchanter is any good, it WILL be the difference between life and death.  If the enchanter is not any good... well... you're in big trouble, so just make sure everyone has SoW.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   and when I say big trouble... I mean BIG TROUBLE.<br><br>I only say this because, if you do not do what the enchanter says, you are turning a situation from 'Ok, we pulled too much but chanter has got it under control' into 'OMG, we're all going to die horrible deaths'.  You could accually be doing more to HURT the group that help.<br><br>Of course, my opinion on this topic may be biased... my sister is an enchanter.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I should note that, like the rest, this is generalized newbieish advice and to be used to give you a better understanding of an often misunderstood class.  I have never played +50.  While I don't come across the inexperienced player too often on FV, it is a MAJOR concern on blue servers, where too many lvl 50's and below think the enchanter is just a buff-whore.  They haste, they breeze, they med... no.<br><br>Don't be that blue-server newbie.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ualyissa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alyissa</A> at: 2/22/02 1:34:32 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usteeltoefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SteeltoeFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/22/02 1:45:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefr